<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%>
	   <a name=100516272660762></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100516272660762><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=4&mid=100516272660762>Equipment worthy of a bard</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=4&mid=100516272660762#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Nov 7th 2:52 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[2.50]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I have found in my experience that having a regen item on your bard can be invaluable.&nbsp;&nbsp;Solo is a great way to lvl up.  I myself use full SS with a fungi tunic.  Once you get your fear song, solo becomes very easy... but like I said, regen becomes very useful.  Due to mobs resisting or the fear breaking you are gonna get whacked.  But if you have regen on, you will usually regen those lost hps when you fear the creature again.  I'm talking about solo in DL atm where mobs are hitting from 60-90.  Anyway, get yourself some regen, at lvl 45 with fungi and heal song I regen 34hps per tick sitting down.  Cut your solo downtime to almost nothing and the loot... go to RM and solo some HG's with no downtime... :P  And for exp like you've never seen, fear kite with a rogue... you get the picture.<br><br>Thraxus 45 rockstar<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
	   </form></table><ul>
<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%>
	   <a name=100528392699031></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100528392699031><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=4&mid=100528392699031>RE: Equipment worthy of a bard</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=4&mid=100528392699031#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Nov 9th 12:32 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Umm...really? Regen items are useful on bards? Never would've guessed...<br><br>= P<br><br>Regen items are 'great ways to level' for anyone that can wear them. Increasing the amount of HP regenerated while sitting reduces downtime, as there's a shorter amount of time between kills. In actuality, bards have the least use for a regen item out of any class that can use them, since they acquire the ability to regenerate at a decent rate from level 6 when they get Hymn of Restoration. Finally, of the items that grant regeneration on a permanent basis, the cheapest I can think of (Iksar BP, 5pts per tick or so) runs probably about 10k, making them somewhat out of reach for non-twinks.<br><br>Point: while all your points are true, they seem rather unecessary.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
