	   <tr><td colspan=2>First of all, half-elves may look cool in armor, but stat-wise, they suck for paladins. Half-elves DO make the best bards however, IMHO, because they're a nice mix of both of the advantages of the wood elf and human bard. Second of all, I'm not flaming the paladin class, but if you're going to play a tank class, go with a warrior or shadow knight. A paladin is a watered down warrior that can cast buffs and heal for a little. A cleric is 80 percent beter at this, and a warrior has around 1/4 more HP. I'd go with the bard, they're not just mana batteries after all! -gasp- Ciao.<br><br>Fermata Lestrade<br>28 bard, Altruistic Elite<br>Brell Serilis<br>"I see dumb people. They're everywhere. They don't even know that they're dumb...some call them democrats."<br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
