	   <tr><td colspan=2>ROFLMAO! Learn to spell, "Anonymous" - hehehe.<br><br>All classes are meant to perform certain functions in groups.&nbsp;&nbsp;This becomes especially important at higher levels during raid situations or 'boss'/dragon fights.<br><br>My Bard is 28 ATM.  And I've tried almost every other class/race combo to get a feel for what parts they play in a group.<br><br>Bards excel at 2 things primarily: 1) Kiting outdoors; and 2) amplifying parties by providing groups multiple (twisted), non-stop, mana-free buff/ debuff/ DD/ DoT/ Mez/ Stuns/ healing/ stamina, depending on the situation.  The second area will save your axe in many occasions if you happen to survive to higher levels.<br><br>Bards AMPLIFY groups.  A bard with instruments can give parties a major edge.  AND Bards can step into the fight with weapons if needed, but obviously this is not our forte'.<br><br>I suspect (since my Bard isn't high enough level yet) that at higher level raids and fights, a Bard should be using instruments to amplify the party, and secondarily keeping and eye out and a weapon ready for mobs aggroing on the casters.<br>&nbsp;<br>~ Excelsius Pulvereus, Zealot and Defender of Albion, Nimue<br>~ Ridil of the 31 song Serenade, Druzzil Ro (Retired)<br>~ Excelsius, Karana's Priest, Druzzil Ro (Retired)</td></tr>
