	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[2.50]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>&nbsp;&nbsp;Bards are without doubt the most interesting and adaptible class in norrath..bards are also very enjoyable to play, which is after all the whole point in playing a game<br> Soloing...We can kite, reverse kite AND charm kite..if anything goes wrong we can run around faster than anything in the game while we heal ourselves till we're ready to go back and finish the mob off- in fact, its near impossible to die as a bard if your smart.<br> Ofcourse theres no question that bards are also great in a group..if in a group of melee types, we have haste, strength, stamina and many other buffs to share with the group. If in a mainly caster group we have the much sought after mana song, and we can tank well if we have healer and caster back-up and two good weapons. We also have many crowd control songs...mez..fear..charm-not to mention our pulling skills using out lament songs.<br> Now on to our skills..we basiclly get every skill available..safe fall..hide..sense traps..disarm traps..track..sneak..forage..etc, etc.<br> My simple advice is that everyone should have a bard as you will really enjoy it- I particularly like the little added incentive to level quickly, as you always have a brand new song to play with after every ding.<br> As to good hunting grounds per level..my root was this - 1-4Qeynos noobie ground 4-7 Qeynos hills (wolves, bears,stray gnolls)7-13 Blackburrow (gnolls..duh!)13-20 Oasis (crocs  and orcs) 20-30 South Karana (Elephants,Aviaks and splitpaws) 30-60 haven't decided yet...<br><br> ~Masetro Furioso 30 bard (halfelf)<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
